# RN Mobile ↔ PWA Feature Parity

The CourtFlow app has two client surfaces that must always stay in sync:

- **RN Mobile** — `mobile/src/` (React Native / Expo)
- **PWA** — `src/` (Next.js)

## Rule

Whenever you modify a feature in one surface, you MUST apply the equivalent change to the other surface before finishing.

## Common pairings

| Feature area | RN Mobile | PWA |
|---|---|---|
| Session history (tab/dashboard) | `mobile/src/screens/staff/SessionTabScreen.tsx` `mobile/src/screens/staff/StaffBossDashboardScreen.tsx` | `src/app/(staff)/staff/dashboard.tsx` |
| Payment cards (per-session detail) | `mobile/src/screens/staff/SessionDetailScreen.tsx` | `src/components/session/StaffSessionPaymentsDetail.tsx` |
| Reclub roster / walk-ins | `mobile/src/components/reclub/ReclubRosterSection.tsx` | `src/components/session/SessionCourtPay.tsx` |
| Payment tab (paid/cancelled/undo) | `mobile/src/screens/staff/PaymentTabScreen.tsx` | `src/components/session/StaffSessionPaymentsDetail.tsx` |
| i18n strings | `mobile/src/lib/tablet-check-in-strings.ts` | `src/i18n/locales/staff/en.json` + `vi.json` |

## Checklist before finishing any task

- [ ] Did I change logic or UI in RN? → Apply the same change in PWA.
- [ ] Did I change logic or UI in PWA? → Apply the same change in RN.
- [ ] Did I add/rename a translation key? → Update both `tablet-check-in-strings.ts` and `en.json`/`vi.json`.
- [ ] Did I change an API response shape? → Update both RN types (`mobile/src/types/api.ts`) and PWA interfaces.
